parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the "Hybrid System Warning" or "Check Charging System" warning indicator illuminates
the vehicle will not start
the battery and maintenance lights appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle's lights, including the headlights, to malfunction or fail, leading to reduced visibility and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The headlights or interior lights fail or malfunction
the oil light will not reset
the electrical system malfunctions when exposed to water.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the safety fuse and battery can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the safety fuse blows out
the battery needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle surges forward while in motion
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical shock can cause physical harm to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The driver and passengers experience an electrical shock after making contact with any exterior metal part of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The burning odor inside the vehicle can be a sign of a potential fire hazard, which can lead to accidents and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Illuminated Warning Lights and Engine Stalling
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of warning lights and engine stalling can increase the risk of accidents and injuries, especially if the vehicle loses motive power while in motion.
symptoms: Check engine warning light and several unknown warning lights illuminated
message "Pull Over and Shut Down Vehicle" displayed
vehicle lost motive power and stalled
check engine warning light remained illuminated after restarting the vehicle.

check engine
ABS
service vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid system can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, stall, or shut down while driving, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. This can also cause anxiety and stress for the driver.
symptoms: The Hybrid Propulsion System message is displayed
the Hybrid Safety Warning light illuminates
the vehicle powers down to 25 mph
the vehicle stalls or shuts down while driving
the vehicle jolts forward and stops abruptly
audible alarms ring
and the dashboard displays warning messages such as "Hybrid System Warning! Immediately stop and do not drive" or "Check Charging System".

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaking can cause damage to the engine and other components, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Engine oil is leaking from the vehicle.
